    codex
    Iâ€™ve wired up a new Dashboard shell that automatically wraps any route under /demo with a responsive sidebar + header, and left
    other pages (like your landing page at /) untouched. Hereâ€™s what I did:

    â€¢ Created a new layouts folder under web/components/layouts with three client-side components:
      â€“ DashboardNav.tsx: sidebar nav with active-link highlighting
      â€“ DashboardHeader.tsx: top bar with a mobile menu toggle
      â€“ DashboardLayout.tsx: glues them together, uses usePathname() to only apply itself on /demo* routes and handles the mobile
    overlay/toggle

    â€¢ Hooked it into your root layout (web/app/layout.tsx), so every page is passed through <DashboardLayout>â€¦</DashboardLayout>

    â€¢ Refactored the two demo pages (web/app/demo/page.tsx and web/app/demo/profile-preview/page.tsx) to drop their own <main>
    wrappersâ€”now they simply render as children under the new layout

    With this in place:

        * Visiting `/demo` or `/demo/profile-preview` gives you the dashboard scaffold.
        * Other routes (e.g. `/`) render exactly as before.

    Let me know if youâ€™d like any tweaks to the styling or the nav items!
